## ⚠️ Common Mistakes

- **"UDP is always faster"** — not if the app has to build its own reliability layer on top; profile before assuming.
- **Firewall blocking handshake packets** — check SYN/SYN-ACK/ACK aren't dropped for TCP; check both directions are open for UDP (harder since there's no connection state to track).
- **App doesn't handle UDP packet loss** — apps expecting ordered/reliable data will break on raw UDP; needs explicit handling.
- **Misreading `netstat` output** — don't confuse LISTEN (waiting for connections) with ESTABLISHED (active connection); understand Recv-Q/Send-Q correctly.

