## 🛡️ Defensive Engineering

### TCP Security

| Threat | Defense |
|---|---|
| **SYN Flood** — flood of SYNs, handshake never completed, ties up server resources | SYN cookies (no resource allocation until ACK returns valid cookie); SYN rate limiting; firewall/IDS rules |
| **TCP Reset (RST) attacks** — forged RST to kill a connection | Strong random initial sequence numbers (ISNs); network segmentation to prevent sniffing |
| **Port scans** (e.g. Nmap) | Firewall — only open necessary ports; IDS to detect scan patterns; rate-limit connection attempts |

### UDP Security

| Threat | Defense |
|---|---|
| **UDP amplification/reflection** — spoofed source IP + small query → server sends huge response to victim | Ingress filtering (drop packets with spoofed source IPs at network edge); rate limiting; disable open "any" queries on DNS servers |
| **UDP flood** — bombard victim with UDP packets | Firewall/IPS blocking; rate limiting; DDoS mitigation services |
| **App-level vulnerabilities** — e.g. game server not validating client data | Robust input validation, careful protocol/state design |

